data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
DropLaunch gives you several convenient ways to get your custom map up and running on a local server.
Drag and Drop: The easiest way to launch a map is to simply drag the .map file from your folder and drop it directly onto the DropLaunch application window. It will automatically create a start file and launch the server for you. You can even drag a map file onto the DropLaunch.exe icon when the app isn't running, and it will boot up a server with that map.
From the Map List: In the "Active Folder" tab, you can right-click on any map to open a context menu. From there, select "Create Start File And Start Server". You can also just double-click on a map in this list to launch it immediately.
From Your History: The "Run History" tab keeps a list of all the maps you've previously launched. You can double-click any entry in this list to quickly start that map again.
From a Notification: If you have the file watcher and desktop notifications enabled, a notification will pop up when you save a new version of your map. Clicking this notification will instantly start a server with that map.

data.name: label32.Text
data.value:
The file watcher will automatically keep an eye on your map files inside your active folder.
Real-Time Monitoring: Monitors the map directory you've specified. It looks for any changes to files with a .map extension.
Instant Updates: If you create, delete, rename, or save a .map file in the monitored folder, the file watcher detects this change and instantly updates the list of maps you see in the "Active Folder" tab.
Desktop Notifications: If you have desktop notifications enabled, the file watcher will also send you a Windows notification whenever a map file is changed.
Quick Launch: You can click directly on the notification to launch a server with the newly saved map, making your testing workflow even faster.
You can enable or disable the file watcher and desktop notifications from the Settings page in the application.

data.name: label34.Text
data.value:
The "Create Prefab Start File and Start Server" option is designed for more focused, isolated testing. This is especially useful when you are working on a specific monument, puzzle, or custom prefab. This start file adds several commands to the server launch to allow map testing of unfinished maps.
+cargoship.event_enabled False Disables the Cargo Ship event.
+baseboat.generate_paths False Stops boats from generating paths.
+ai.ocean_patrol_path_iterations 0 Disables AI pathing for ocean patrols.
+server.events False Turns off most random server events.
+antihack.terrain_protection 0 Disables some anti-hacking measures related to terrain, which can be useful when testing building mechanics or custom terrain features.
It’s perfect for ensuring a custom monument works correctly or for fine-tuning a puzzle.

data.name: label33.Text
data.value:
After launching a server, DropLaunch can automatically copy the connection command to your clipboard if you've enabled this option in the setup. The command is usually "connect localhost:28015"
(Optionally make yourself admin before joining the server, read below) Press F1 in game to open up the console and type connect localhost:28015 command and press enter.
Find Your SteamID64: You'll need your unique SteamID64. A quick way to find this is to use a website like https://steamid.io/
In your server console (black screen thats running) run the command "ownerid 123456677890" Make sure that you replace the number with your unique SteamID64 The console should tell you that you are now a owner.
Run the command "writecfg" to save your admin status to the server files.

data.value:
uMod is a plugin framework that lets server owners extend and customize game behavior without modifying the game’s core files.
Run custom server plugins written in C#, Lua, Python, or JavaScript (though C# is the most common) Modify game mechanics (e.g., add teleport commands, kits, custom spawns) Create admin tools, permissions systems, economy plugins, etc. Easily manage server rules, gameplay logic, and automation
Downloads the official latest release from the Umod website. Extracts the files to the root directory used for server files. Deletes the .zip file downloaded.
More info on Umod.org
